Wyclife Agumba Oluoch

Bio

I am a Spatial Ecologist who uses Ecological Niche Modeling theory and applications to understand and explain influence of global change on distribution of species. In that process, I largely rely on big data and open source programming platforms such as R for ease of extensibility and reproducibility of all analytical steps.

Education

University of Bonn | NRW - Bonn, Germany

PhD in Ecology and Natural Resource Management | October 2019 - Present

Maseno University | Maseno, Kenya

M.A. in Geography | September 2013 - December 2018

Moi University | Eldoret, Kenya

B.A. in Geography | August 2008 - August 2012

Experience

Environmentalist Intern | KALRO - Tea Research Institute | May 2015 - October 2019
